<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="443" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1460,2026]" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1460,1486]" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from other species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kamiya" authorityYear="1963" box="[1039,1199,1460,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1039,1199,1460,1486]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Axinoscymnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a single elongate oval dark brown spot on each elytron (
<figureCitation box="[583,665,1496,1522]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,491,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-171@13.[151,1436,474,1567]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Axinoscymnus puttarudriahi Kapur et Munshi, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–f: 0.05 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Fig. 8a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="444" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1460,2026]" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1532,1558]" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Description.</emphasis>
TL: 
<quantity box="[402,568,1532,1558]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.455" metricValueMax="1.62" metricValueMin="1.29" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" unit="mm" value="1.455" valueMax="1.62" valueMin="1.29">1.29–1.62 mm</quantity>
, TW: 
<quantity box="[638,804,1532,1558]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.005" metricValueMax="1.13" metricValueMin="0.88" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" unit="mm" value="1.005" valueMax="1.13" valueMin="0.88">0.88–1.13 mm</quantity>
, TH: 
<quantity box="[869,1034,1532,1558]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="7.7" metricValueMin="6.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" unit="mm" value="0.7" valueMax="0.77" valueMin="0.63">0.63–0.77 mm</quantity>
, TL/TW: 1.43–1.47, EL/EW: 1.13– 1.17, PL/PW: 0.55–0.57, HW/PW: 0.67–0.7, PW/EW: 0.65–0.69.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1460,2026]" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">
Body oval, moderately convex, dorsum with white pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[938,1054,1604,1630]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,491,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-171@13.[151,1436,474,1567]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Axinoscymnus puttarudriahi Kapur et Munshi, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–f: 0.05 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Figs 8a–c</figureCitation>
). Head, antennae and mouthparts dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[300,384,1640,1666]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,491,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-171@13.[151,1436,474,1567]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Axinoscymnus puttarudriahi Kapur et Munshi, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–f: 0.05 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Fig. 8c</figureCitation>
), tip of mandibles blackish brown. Pronotum and scutellar shield dark brown. Elytra black with a single elongate oval dark brown spot on each elytron (
<figureCitation box="[833,914,1676,1702]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,491,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-171@13.[151,1436,474,1567]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Axinoscymnus puttarudriahi Kapur et Munshi, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–f: 0.05 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Fig. 8a</figureCitation>
). Prothoracic hypomeron and prosternum dark brown. Mesoventrite and elytral epipleurae dark brown. Metaventrite black. Legs yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1460,2026]" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">
Head with fine frontal punctures, as large as eye facets, 1.0–2.0 diameters apart. Eyes densely faceted, interocular distance about 0.33 times of head width (
<figureCitation box="[725,807,1784,1810]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,491,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-171@13.[151,1436,474,1567]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Axinoscymnus puttarudriahi Kapur et Munshi, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–f: 0.05 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Fig. 8c</figureCitation>
). Pronotal punctures slightly larger than those on frons, 1.0–2.0 diameters apart. Surface of elytra with punctures much larger than those on pronotum, separated by 1.0–2.5 diameters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1460,2026]" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">
Abdominal postcoxal lines complete and moderately recurved, reaching 3/4 length of ventrite 1 (
<figureCitation box="[1286,1368,1892,1919]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,491,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-171@13.[151,1436,474,1567]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Axinoscymnus puttarudriahi Kapur et Munshi, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–f: 0.05 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Fig. 8d</figureCitation>
), area enclosed by the lines finely and sparsely punctate, irregularly distributed, broadly smooth along the lines; ventrite 1 with coarse and sparse punctures at middle, irregularly distributed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1460,2026]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1437,151,465]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="444" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">
Male genitalia. Penis slender, base of penis slightly broadened, narrowing to apex (
<figureCitation box="[1128,1210,2000,2026]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,491,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-171@13.[151,1436,474,1567]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Axinoscymnus puttarudriahi Kapur et Munshi, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–f: 0.05 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Fig. 8e</figureCitation>
); tegmen with penis guide widest at base, gradually tapering to apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[866,945,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,491,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-171@13.[151,1436,474,1567]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Axinoscymnus puttarudriahi Kapur et Munshi, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–f: 0.05 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="444">Fig. 8f</figureCitation>
), longer than 2/3 length of parameres; parameres stout and elongate oval with several setae at apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[960,1039,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,491,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-171@13.[151,1436,474,1567]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Axinoscymnus puttarudriahi Kapur et Munshi, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–f: 0.05 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="444">Fig. 8f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
